Introduction

Kim Myung Soo, better known by the stage name L, is a South Korean singer and actor under Look Media and Infinite Company. He is best known as the lead vocalist and visual of the boy group INFINITE.

He debuted with INFINITE in 2010 and later expanded his career into acting, appearing in several dramas. In 2019, he left Woollim Entertainment and joined Management 2sang shortly after in 2020. He made his solo debut in 2021 with the single album 'Memory'. After leaving Management 2sang in 2023, he signed with Look Media.

L's Japanese debut came in November 2023 with the single 'Moments'. In 2024, he announced the release of his first EP, '24/7'. Myungsoo also completed his mandatory military service in 2022, where he was involved in a military musical.
